![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

The use of `setTimeout` here is unnecessary and degrades the user experience by introducing artificial delays. Since the Tauri command `auto_install_blackhole_command` is asynchronous and internally waits for the `osascript` (and thus the installer) to complete, the response is only received once the installation process has finished. You should perform the status check and transition to the next step immediately after the `invoke` promise resolves.

```
      const response = await invoke<{ data: BlackHoleInstallResult }>(
        "auto_install_blackhole_command",
      );
      setInstallResult(response.data);

      await checkBlackHoleStatus();
      if (response.data.success || response.data.method === "manual") {
        setCurrentStep("complete");
      }
```
